===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|minc|e}}

# To walk with short steps; to walk in a prim, affected manner.
#:''The daughters of Zion are haughty, and walk with  stretched forth necks and wanton eyes, mincing       as they go.'' --[[Is.]] III. 16.
#:''I'll turn two mincing steps Into a manly  stride.'' &mdash; [[w:Shakespeare|Shakespeare]]
# To act or talk with affected nicety; to affect delicacy in manner.

